# Copy to .env.local for local development. The playground needs no env vars
# at all for local (`kind: "local"`) targets.
#
# Remote (`kind: "url"`) targets may name an env var in "target.authHeaderEnv"
# (convention: PLAYGROUND_<SCREAMING_SNAKE_ID>_AUTH). The proxy reads that var
# via `process.env[name]` indirection — the name comes from agents.config.json
# at runtime, so it cannot be listed here exhaustively. Its value is the FULL
# Authorization header the agent expects, e.g. "Bearer <token>". Example for
# an entry with "authHeaderEnv": "PLAYGROUND_CODE_REVIEWER_AUTH":
PLAYGROUND_CODE_REVIEWER_AUTH=
